The paper discusses the security, privacy, and ethical risks associated with the collection and use of high-resolution individual geolocation data, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the potential use of this data for public good, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper touches on the measurement of segregation in cities and transit modeling, which falls under the category of social and economic systems (cs.SOC).
